{"type":"message","id":"ce1c7716","parentId":"f3a4c2db","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:18:06.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context-engine I installed is a C-suite advisor context management skill - it's not the \"Context-Engine\" from the article which is about token compression and smart context management for AI conversations.\n\nThe article was about OpenClaw's Context-Engine for \"智能上下文管理、无损压缩\" (intelligent context management, lossless compression). This is likely a built-in feature of OpenClaw itself, not a skill that can be installed via clawhub.\n\nThe installed \"context-engine\" skill is actually about loading company context for C-suite advisors - completely different.\n\nI should let the user know about this confusion. The \"Context-Engine\" from the article is likely a built-in OpenClaw feature (possibly the Context-Engine mentioned in the docs), not a clawhub skill.\n","thinkingSignature":"7b2453b1174b6866ccca49cec12f14a7171f4f9525b2d6bcdc675ce7767c74fe"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n装好了，但有个问题要说明——\n\n我装的这个 `context-engine` 是**另一个东西**，是\"企业高管顾问上下文管理\"工具，跟你发的那篇\"智能上下文管理、无损压缩\"不是一回事。\n\n那篇文章说的 Context-Engine，大概率是 **OpenClaw 内置的功能**，不是插件市场里的 skill。\n\n让我查一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iycv2v9cig08_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"context.engine\\|ContextEngine\\|context_engine\" ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":160,"output":287,"cacheRead":27968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28415,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778663856330,"responseId":"065374b0f6acd9ed9a429fb3046d96f4"}}
