{"type":"message","id":"4d3d8365","parentId":"e4479b2a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:37:12.708Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key issue is clear now. The error message says:\n\n\"Stock lossless-claw 0.2.7 expects OpenClaw plugin runtime support from PR #41090 (https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/41090). OpenClaw 2026.3.8 and 2026.3.8-beta.1 do not include merge commit 4790e40; the first OpenClaw release after 2026.3.8 is required for stock lossless-claw 0.2.7 without this fallback patch.\"\n\nSo there's a version mismatch. The installed lossless-claw is 0.9.4 from npm (which calls itself \"stock lossless-claw 0.2.7\" in the error), but it's designed to work with a version of OpenClaw that includes PR #41090 - which the current OpenClaw (2026.3.8) doesn't have.\n\n\nThe plugin did initialize and the database was created, but there are compatibility warnings that might affect how well it works. I should check what version of OpenClaw is currently installed to see if there's a newer release available that includes the necessary patch.\n","thinkingSignature":"3726dd9e91469e3e799dd55c7dc8b782ede7bdf5f77684aaf4ee198c1ef7e604"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fjfy7hgyhim5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/package.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('version','?'))\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1746,"output":319,"cacheRead":52864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54929,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778664995051,"responseId":"0653792383d2c0d14ba6862c246fc0e8"}}
