{"type":"message","id":"cdf9e117","parentId":"51a6ee39","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:38:08.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying the response speed is getting slow. Let me think about what could be causing this.\n\nLooking at the situation:\n1. We just installed lossless-claw 0.9.4 from npm\n2. Then we ran `openclaw plugins install @martian-engineering/lossless-claw` which installed it into ~/.openclaw/npm/\n3. The gateway restarted and loaded the plugin\n4. Now lossless-claw 0.2.7 is showing in the logs (stock lossless-claw 0.2.7)\n\nThere seem to be two versions - the globally npm installed 0.9.4 and the stock 0.2.7 that OpenClaw's plugin system resolved.\n \nThe output shows \"Stock lossless-claw 0.2.7\" and mentions compatibility issues with OpenClaw 2026.3.8, so the plugin appears to be running but with a fallback that might be affecting performance. The gateway is consuming 8.4% CPU with 544MB memory, which could indicate the LCM database operations are causing some overhead.\n\nThe slow responses could stem from several sources: LCM's DAG summarization adds processing overhead, the database might be undergoing initial indexing, the compaction algorithm could be consuming resources, or there may be unnecessary re-initializations happening. I need to check the logs to determine what's actually causing the slowdown.\n","thinkingSignature":"10a91174fc1a715172921d44cf5bd5f479912ff12ebd5cd307485085051683fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ab6g16a43mxu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -100 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-05-13.log 2>&1 | grep -E \"lcm|slow|compaction|latency|error\" | tail -40","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4448,"output":365,"cacheRead":50432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55245,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778665053297,"responseI