{"type":"message","id":"13ea8cc8","parentId":"4c976a0e","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:39:55.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The installed version is 0.9.4 which is the latest. But the CLI is showing 0.2.7 as the stock version that has compatibility issues. This means there might be a bundled version of lossless-claw inside OpenClaw's stock extensions, while the npm-installed one (0.9.4) is what we want to use.\n\nThe warning about \"Stock lossless-claw 0.2.7\" suggests OpenClaw's bundled plugins include an older lossless-claw. But the actual loaded plugin is from the npm installation at 0.9.4.\n\nLet me check what OpenClaw shows in plugins list and which version is actually running.\n\n\nThe gateway restart likely loaded the npm version 0.9.4 instead of the stock 0.2.7, and the CLI errors are just from calling a command that doesn't exist in the way I tried it. The plugin itself initialized properly with the minimax model at 0.75 threshold, so the compatibility issue might be resolved now that we're on the newer version.\n","thinkingSignature":"b905ebb0e29287975e403420748c8298b081581da95f0b10df493c72c3583403"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tj8tk9ivs8kp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -200 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-05-13.log 2>&1 | grep -E \"error|warn|slow|latency|compaction\" | tail -30","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":331,"output":294,"cacheRead":55936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56561,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778665166717,"responseId":"065379cf68f2b203d210e9f3cf0ef63b"}}
