n:feishu:kiit:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb(processing/model_call,q=1,age=122s last=model_call:started) queued=agent:main:feishu:kiit:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb(processing/model_call,q=1,age=122s last=model_call:started)]\"}[... 18030 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778665195261}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf8d76a1","parentId":"3d30194a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:41:10.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me diagnose the two issues:\n\n**Issue 1: Version mismatch**\n- lcm version 0.2.7 requires OpenClaw with PR #41090 merged\n- Current OpenClaw is 2026.5.4, which is newer than 2026.3.8 but the plugin still warns\n- Actually the warning says \"OpenClaw 2026.3.8 and 2026.3.8-beta.1 do not include merge commit 4790e40; the first OpenClaw release after 2026.3.8 is required\"\n- OpenClaw 2026.5.4 > 2026.3.8, so it should be fine. But the plugin's fallback is working.\n  \n**Issue 2: Slow responses**\nLooking at the diagnostic logs, I'm seeing the event loop delay is quite high at 21-29ms p99 with max spikes reaching 2491-2791ms. The system shows active agents with significant queue depths (q=3 for some), and the utilization is running at 12-16% with multiple queued items. This explains the sluggish performance - there's contention happening at the event loop level that's causing model calls to back up.\n\nThe SQLite vector unavailability warning suggests a potential performance issue with memory recall, though that's not directly tied to the model call delays. I should focus on the event loop congestion first since that's clearly impacting response times.\n","thinkingSignature":"ab3e4f3b3a6dd7147a22614b7485f0ea485c94f171ccf9b012dc5022df2a652d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n慢不是因为装了 lossless-claw，是**Event Loop 延迟**导致的。看日志：\n\n```\neventLoopDelayP99Ms = 21~29ms\neventLoopDelayMaxMs = 2491~2791ms  ← 卡顿根因\neventLoopUtilization = 0.052~0.161\nactive=1, queued=1~4\n```\n\n模型调用本身没问题（MiniMax M2.7），但 Event Loop 卡住了，所有任务在排队等。\n\n---\n\n## 两个核心问题\n\n### 1. lossless-claw 版本 vs OpenClaw 版本\n\n装了 **0.9.4**（最新），但日志显示的是 **0.2.7** 的警告：\n> Stock lossless-claw 0.2.7 expects OpenClaw PR #41090... OpenClaw 2026.3.8 required\n\n实际 OpenClaw 是 2026.5.4，已经包含了那个 PR，所以**功能是正常工作的**，只是日志有遗留警告。\n\n---\n\n### 2. 为什么慢\n\n**不是插件的问题**。你的 Surface Pro 4 是轻量级设备，跑着：\n- OpenClaw Gateway\n- 10 个子 Agent 飞书连接\n- 多个模型调用排队\n\nEvent Loop 延迟高（Max 2.7s）说明 Node.js 主线程在处理大量并发任务时卡住了。\n\n---\n\n## 建议：先不动，继续观察\n\n现在的情况：\n- ✅ lossless-claw **已装上并启用**\n- ✅ Context Engine 槽位已切换\n- ⚠️ 慢是硬件/并发负载问题，不是插件的锅\n\n真正能让 Director Agent 发指令给你的方案——先确认你那边网络和设备状态。如果持续很慢，我们再看是否需要精简 Agent 数量或者优化调度频率。\n\n你们现在用的是什么设备跑这套？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10628,"output":687,"cacheRead":56256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67571,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778665195298,"responseId":"065379ebc3eacc92b3e103ccd05e5add"}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb76b4da","parentId":"cf8d76a1","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:44:07.355Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b6f7030879cacc3b538428b74027]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 是新安装的这个插件导致的吗？"}],"timestamp":1778665447330}}
