{"type":"message","id":"a12b5058","parentId":"6390d98b","timestamp":"2026-05-13T09:46:19.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has 3 questions:\n1. What do I suggest for the communication channel between Director and other Agents?\n2. Why is the response suddenly slow when there's nothing else running in the background?\n3. Does the enterprise Context Engine (lossless-claw) actually work/useful?\n\nLet me address each one:\n\n**Q2: Why suddenly slow?**\nLooking at the logs, the main kiit session was ALREADY slow before lossless-claw was installed. The session `082779a9-a57f-43bb-ac52-7d16968de9c0` was reporting long-running since 17:19 (before we installed lossless-claw at ~17:30). This means the slow response is NOT caused by lossless-claw installation.\n\n\nThe sluggishness traces back to queued model calls—multiple long-running sessions are stacking up in the queue, and the MiniMax model API itself appears to be the bottleneck rather than any recent changes on our end.\n\n**Q3: Does lossless-claw work?**\nYes, it's working. It's installed as the active Context Engine (confirmed by `openclaw plugins list` showing it enabled and the contextEngine slot set to \"lossless-claw\"). The warnings in the log are about version compatibility with OpenClaw's plugin runtime support, which is a separate concern from whether it's actually functioning.\n\nThe plugin uses DAG-based summarization with incremental compaction to manage conversation context, which should reduce token usage over time—but whether that's noticeable depends on how the user interacts with the system. Right now it's still new, so the benefits haven't had time to compound yet.\n\n**Q1: Suggestions for Agent communication**\n\nFor the Director Agent to distribute tasks, I'm considering whether a task pool with cron-based polling would be more efficient than relying on the feishu channel. The Director would need its own dedicated session and a way to actively check for new work rather than just waiting for messages.\n","thinkingSignature":"ab1d905d6369b4dd65b1da1af93a34a349860f0524cb0830b5665321ca1785de"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_298l6j4ovnvq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -E \"openclaw|node\" | grep -v grep | grep -v \"systemd\" | head -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":563,"output":457,"cacheRead":66208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67228,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778665563180,"responseId":"06537b5b7901c15d07e1f17558cd3cae"}}
