{"type":"message","id":"5d397376","parentId":"0ae899cd","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:31:07.745Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me set up the architecture. I need to think about this properly:\n\n1. **Team Registry** - define which teams exist, which agents belong to which team\n2. **Task Pool** - shared task file in JSON\n3. **Director Cron** - periodic task distribution\n4. **Agent configs** - each agent knows its team and can communicate internally\n\nThe key insight from HALEI's message:\n- \"跨境电商team来互通，后边建其他team的时候就不互通了\"\n- \"通过选人的方式来很方便地调整\"\n\nThis means teams are configurable groups of agents. I should design a team registry that maps agents to teams, and the Director's coordination logic reads from this.\n\n\nI'll start by setting up the directory structure, then create a team registry file that defines which agents belong to the cross-border team, configure the task pool, and get the Director ready to poll and dispatch tasks. The team registry will eventually support multiple teams, but we're starting with just the cross-border team for now.","thinkingSignature":"f39812716e10002b428238662a028f3d096f3c49aaf50758df3445812014a700"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6qtxhuzeswn5_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"{\n  \"version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"teams\": {\n    \"cross-border\": {\n      \"name\": \"跨境电商团队\",\n      \"agents\": [\"director\", \"tts\", \"content\", \"traffic\", \"ops\", \"koc\", \"finance\", \"review\"],\n      \"enabled\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"defaultTeam\": \"cross-border\"\n}","path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/teams/registry.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":89,"output":332,"cacheRead":69344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69765,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778671853274,"responseId":"065393ee94ccff7d150d60c49d5a1672"}}
