{"type":"message","id":"592a763a","parentId":"a53b7d56","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:32:38.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the `__dirname` resolves to the parent directory because the script is at `~/.openclaw/workspace/teams/cross-border/director-coordinator.js` but `join(__dirname, '..')` resolves to `~/.openclaw/workspace/teams/` not `~/.openclaw/workspace/`. \n\nWait, I need to recalculate:\n- `__dirname` = `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/teams/cross-border`\n- `join(__dirname, '..')` = `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/teams`\n\n\n- `TASK_POOL` = `join(TEAM_DIR, 'tasks', 'task-pool.json')` = `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/teams/tasks/task-pool.json`\n\nBut this file doesn't exist at that path. The actual file is at `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/teams/cross-border/tasks/task-pool.json`. The real problem is my path construction logic is wrong—`TEAM_DIR` points to the teams directory, but I need to account for the cross-border subdirectory structure when building the task pool path. I see the issue now - `join(__dirname, '..')` resolves to `teams/` directory, but the task file is nested deeper at `cross-border/tasks/`. I need to trace the path more carefully: with `__dirname` as the script directory, `join(__dirname, '..')` only goes up one level, not to where the tasks folder actually is. I need to hardcode the path since the directory structure is clear: tasks are at `cross-border/tasks/task-pool.json` relative to the workspace root.\n","thinkingSignature":"0e73285429304b4461f2629dfd0501091b01e6bb9f454a0665ea42a61639b0bf"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n路径算错了，修复一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zt3wjw4jh7xz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node --input-type=module << 'EOF'\nimport { join, dirname } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\n// director-coordinator.js 里 __dirname 的值\nconst scriptDir = '/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/teams/cross-border';\ncons