{"type":"message","id":"277d90ad","parentId":"4ecd0c55","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:33:27.766Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now the task-pool is updated. Let me check the status and also think about the cron setup. The key parts are:\n\n1. The coordinator script works\n2. Now I need to set up a cron job that runs the Director agent periodically\n3. The Director agent needs to actually send messages via sessions_send\n\nBut actually, the coordinator.js is just a prototype script. The actual Director agent is one of the OpenClaw agents (with ID \"director\"). The cron job should trigger the Director agent to run this coordinator logic.\n\nLet me think about the full architecture:1. A cron job runs periodically (every 30 min or so)2. The cron triggers an isolated agent session that runs the coordinator logic\n3. The coordinator reads the task pool, sends tasks via sessions_send to the target agents4. The coordinator writes results back\n\nBut wait - sessions_send requires the main session context. And each agent has its own session. \n\nActually, looking at the architecture again:\n- The \"director\" is an OpenClaw agent with its own feishu account\n- It can receive messages via feishu\n- It can send messages via sessions_send\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. You tell KIIT (via feishu): \"本周任务安排：选品+内容\"\n2. KIIT writes tasks to the task pool\n3. Every 30 min, the Director agent's cron runs and processes the task pool\n4. Director uses sessions_send to dispatch tasks to sub-agents\n\nBut actually there's a simpler approach that's more aligned with OpenClaw's design:\n- Just use sessions_send directly from the cron job (which runs an agent)\n- That agent reads the task pool and sends messages to the target agents\n\nLet me set up the cron now. The cron should trigger an isolated agent that runs the coordinator script.\n\n\nThe cron is straightforward - every 30 minutes, an isolated agent session will execute the coordinator script which reads the task pool, dispatches via sessions_send to sub-agents, then writes results back. I need to add a teams module structure with a registry and task pool files to make this self-contained.\n\nNow I'm setting up the Director's periodic execution to pick up pending tasks from the pool and dispatch them to the appropriate sub-agents.","thinkingSignature":"eab09a8d0eb36a63579b45367c545c1aece62910174bf62944464bb30918edba"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nCoordinator 跑通了。现在设置 Director 的定时调度：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b6ge5zzouchh_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"delivery":{"mode":"announce"},"enabled":true,"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"你是一个任务协调引擎。读取任务池 /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/teams/cross-border/tasks/task-pool.json，找出所有 status=pending 的任务，通过 sessions_send 将每个任务发送给对应的 agent（agentId 分别为: tts, content, traffic, ops, koc, finance, review）。发送后，将任务状态改为 dispatched。示例：\nconst task = {id: 'task_001', type: '选品', to: ['tts'], content: '...'}\nawait sessions_send({agentId: 'tts', message: `【任务】${task.content}`})\n然后回复：任务已调度完成"},"schedule":{"expr":"*/30 * * * *","kind":"cron","tz":"Asia/Shanghai"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":374,"output":716,"cacheRead":72928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74018,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778671993004,"responseId":"065394794034a9f7357bcfac998304db"}}
